The 0.5s filter is applied only to non-leaf (internal) nodes. All 899 leaf nodes (each 0.13s — a single sampled   
frame) are kept unconditionally.                                                                                  

We retain only nodes whose
duration is larger than 0.5 seconds, ensuring that each segment is semantically meaningful.

